    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 172.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Scruggs</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 19, 1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 74.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 239, of the 2d of
                    October, referring to the proposed establishment by Colombia of custom-houses at
                    Colon and Panama, and detailing your action in the direction of preventing this
                    and providing for the continued freedom of the Isthmian transit.</p>
                <p>Your action is quite consistent with that contemplated by one of the
                    instructions—No. 2, of November 3—just given to the new minister, Mr. Jacob, on
                    the same subject.</p>
                <p>I inclose a copy of that instruction.<note n="†" xml:id="d172fn1">For Inclosure,
                        see document No. 170, <ref target="#pg_223">page 223</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
